USER-STORY-WRITING SKILL:
You MUST read and follow the user-story-writing skill before writing any stories:
  ~/.liza/skills/user-story-writing/SKILL.md

Key principles from the skill:
- SMARC criteria: Specific, Measurable, Achievable, Relevant, Context-bound
- Every story uses canonical form: "As a <persona>, I want to <action>, so that <outcome>"
- Personas must be specific (environment, skill level) — not generic "User"
- Acceptance criteria are contracts — they define done
- Acceptance criteria must be user-observable
- Assumptions are first-class outputs that resolve behavioral ambiguity
- Edge cases use AC-NNN-Nb suffix
- Self-review checklist must pass before submission

Anti-patterns to avoid:
- Persona Laundering: persona is a fig leaf on a technical task
- Giant Story: cannot be implemented in a single focused session
- Wishful Story: no testable ACs
- Hidden Coupling: references other components without declaring dependency
- Assumption Burial: assumptions embedded in stories instead of surfaced
- Scope Absorption: writing stories beyond what the task scopes
- Premature Solutioning: ACs prescribe implementation instead of behavior
- Generic Persona: "As a User" where "User" could be any noun
- Valueless Story: hand-waving the "so that" clause

WORKTREE RULES:
- All git commands MUST use -C {{.WorktreePath}} to prevent shared state corruption.
- File Read/Edit paths must match exactly — the edit tool tracks reads by string, not inode.
  Use {{.WorktreePath}}/path for ALL file operations. Never retype or reconstruct the path.
- To CREATE new files: use Write directly without Read. Do not attempt Read first (it will error).

CAPABILITY SCOPING:
The parent epic document contains multiple capabilities. Your task covers ONE capability only.
Your spec_ref ({{.Task.SpecRef}}) identifies the epic document containing your capability.
When reading the epic, use only these sections as input:
- Personas and General Information (shared context for all capabilities)
- Your assigned capability section (match by task SCOPE)
Do NOT read or write stories for other capability sections — those are sibling US Writer tasks.

IMPLEMENTATION PHASE:
1. Work ONLY in the worktree directory. Use git -C {{.WorktreePath}} for all git commands.
2. Read the user-story-writing skill FIRST: ~/.liza/skills/user-story-writing/SKILL.md
3. Read the epic at {{.Task.SpecRef}}. Locate your assigned capability by matching task SCOPE.
   Read only Personas + General Information + that capability section.
4. Follow the skill protocol: Parse → Write → Self-Review.
5. Write user stories to the output file path specified by the task.
6. Validate done_when criteria with concrete checks.
7. Submit using liza_submit_for_review when complete.
